item.title: CVE-2020-8896|2024-08-04T10:12:11.000Z -- google%20llc -- google%20earth%20pro
item.description: A Buffer Overflow vulnerability in the khcrypt implementation in Google Earth Pro versions up to and including 7.3.2 allows an attacker to perform a Man-in-the-Middle attack using a specially crafted key to read data past the end of the buffer used to hold it. Mitigation: Update to Google Earth Pro 7.3.3.
